external_knowledge:
- Time rank refers to the order of plasma concentration measurements within a study; 
- A time rank greater than 1 means excluding the first measurement (or starting point) of the study; 
- Study time refers to the duration of the study; 
- Concentration rank refers to the order of plasma concentration values within a study, with higher concentrations having a lower rank.

sql:
SELECT AVG(plasma_concentration) AS average_plasma_concentration
FROM studies
WHERE analyte = 'Wyeth-14643';

